<item>
            <title>[LU-6671] Wireshark: LDLM_ENQUEUE reply with undecoded buffer</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6671</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The attached file is the tcpdump on a client where I ran a &quot;truncate&quot; test (&apos;multiop &amp;lt;file&amp;gt; OTc 1024&apos;). After the MDS_REINT request and reply there is an LDLM_ENQUEUE request and reply for an extent lock. The &quot;verbose&quot; tshark output shows in the header that there are three buffers:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Lm Buflens: 152&lt;br/&gt;
    Lm Buflens: 112&lt;br/&gt;
    Lm Buflens: 56&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But only the first two &apos;ptlrpc_body&apos; and &apos;ldlm_reply&apos; get decoded or even mentioned. I am guessing the thrid buffer is an ost_lvb, but I could well be wrong.&lt;br/&gt;
-Andrew&lt;/p&gt;</description>
